Meet <b>Allie</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Allie lives in Westridge at <a href='/home/?user=the_rebels'>5950 Broken Tree Bend</a>, in a house boasting a magnificent view of the town.  She has been a citizen since May 14, 2005, and is really having a blast here in Millsberry.<br><br>Despite her short time as a citizen, Allie has already made many friends, thanks to her friendly and outgoing nature.  She's never too shy to meet new people, so be sure to say hi if you happen to see her!  Allie's friends say that she always makes time for getting to know people, and loves making new friends.  Allie's favorite place to hang out is at her best friend's house, where she and her buddies often meet up on lazy afternoons.<br><br>Allie also likes participating in a variety of team sports with her friends, as she is a very athletic person.  Her favorite sport is hockey, and those who have played with Allie speak admiringly of her pinpoint passes and blazing speed on the ice.  During the summer, don't be surprised if you find her escaping the heat by playing some hockey at a nearby rink.  In fact, ice rinks are among her favorite places to hang out, year round!  If you happen to be at a rink in the area, you might spot her out on the ice; she'll be the one sporting all black, as that is her favorite color.<br><br>Allie's not just a fan of frozen water, though.  Her other favorite place to hang out is by the pool, so expect to see lots of her there with the hot weather coming on.  While she usually swims several laps for a good athletic workout, Allie also enjoys just hanging around at the pool, splashing water, jumping off the diving board, and talking to friends.<br><br>Her main love, however, is music.  Allie's huge collection of punk and classic rock CDs is legendary among her friends, and she is constantly adding to it.  Her own musical talent is singing, and she often entertains houseguests with vocal renditions of her favorite songs.  She recently applied her talent and love of music to mixing <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=the_rebels">her own tracks</a> at the Millsberry Recording Studio.  Even though her musical career is just beginning, Allie's work has already made an appearance in Cinnamon Toast Crunch's Top 10 Saved Hits list! <br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Allie, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
